PART 9: PHASE TRANSITIONS IN THE INDEPENDENCE POLYNOMIAL
======================================================================

Roots of I(P_k, x) for k = 2, 3, ..., 10:
  P_2: roots ≈ []
  P_3: roots ≈ [-0.38197]
  P_4: roots ≈ [-0.33333]
  P_5: roots ≈ [-0.6431, -0.30798]
  P_6: roots ≈ [-1.70711, -0.29289]
