  The largest root → -1/φ² = -0.381966 as k → ∞
  This is the HARD-CORE LATTICE GAS critical fugacity for Z!
  x_c(Z) = -1/φ² (1D chain), x_c(Z²) ≈ 3.796 (2D square lattice)

======================================================================
PART 10: THE TOPOLOGICAL UNIVERSE
======================================================================

THE MAP OF THE TOURNAMENT WORLD:

  TOPOLOGICAL LAYER (x = -1):
    Euler characteristic χ = I(Ω, -1)
    Period-6 from SL(2,Z) action
    M^6 = I in the modular group
    Independence complex Ind(Ω) has cyclic homology

  COMBINATORIAL LAYER (x = 1):
    #independent cycle sets = I(Ω, 1)
    α_odd = (I(Ω,1) - I(Ω,-1))/2
    α_even = (I(Ω,1) + I(Ω,-1) - 2)/2

  ARITHMETIC LAYER (x = 2):
    H = I(Ω, 2) = Hamiltonian path count
    Always odd (Rédei)
    Forbidden values from α₁ gaps

  THE BRIDGE FORMULA:
    H + 2χ = 3 + 6α₂ + 6α₃ + 18α₄ + ...
    At n ≤ 5: H + 2χ = 3 EXACTLY
    At n = 6: first correction from α₂

  THE CRITICAL POINTS:
    x = -1/4: double eigenvalue (phase boundary)
    x = -1/φ²: hard-core gas critical fugacity
    x = 0: contractible (trivial)
    x = 1: golden ratio eigenvalue
    x = 2: tournament fugacity
    x = k(k+1): oblong integer-eigenvalue hierarchy
